        <Parent_String>Equus caballus (species) [300250148], Equus (genus) [300265977], Equidae (family) [300265958], Perissodactyla (order) [300310323], Mammalia (class) [300265707], Vertebrata (subphylum) [300265720], Chordata (phylum) [300266513], Animalia (kingdom) [300249395], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breed of horse characterized by a distinctive head shape, high tail carriage, fine bone structure, concave profile, arched neck, a comparatively level croup, and known for speed, stamina, beauty, intelligence, and gentleness. It is believed to be one of the oldest horse breeds, with archaeological evidence dating to 4,500 years before present. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>特色為其獨特的頭型，高尾，健美的骨頭結構，側面顯內凹，頸部呈弓形，臀部則相對較平坦，以速度、耐力、健美、聰明與溫和著名。普遍認為此為最古老的一種馬，且有四千五百年前的考古學證據支持。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
